            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"foot\"><span class=\"c3\">52</span> (<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000030\">return</$link>)<br>\n[ surgat Mephistophilis, quod tumerarisâ The later 4tos have &quot;surgat Mephistophilis DRAGON, quod tumeraris.&quot;âThere is a corruption here, which seems to defy emendation. For &quot;quod TUMERARIS,&quot; Mr. J. Crossley, of Manchester, would read (rejecting the word &quot;Dragon&quot;) &quot;quod TU MANDARES&quot; (the construction being &quot;quod tu mandares ut Mephistophilis appareat et surgat&quot;): but the &quot;tu&quot; does not agree with the preceding &quot;vos.&quot;âThe Revd. J. Mitford proposes &quot;surgat Mephistophilis, per Dragon (or Dagon) quod NUMEN EST AERIS.&quot;]</p></div>"
        },
