            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"foot\"><span class=\"c3\">104</span> (<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000030\">return</$link>)<br>\n[ Seek to saveâ Qy. &quot;Seek THOU to save&quot;? But see note ||, p. 18.]</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">Â Â Â  [Note ||, from page 18 (The First Part of Tamburlaine The\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Great):\n<br>\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Barbarousâ Qy. &quot;O Barbarous&quot;? in the next line but one,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  &quot;O treacherous&quot;? and in the last line of the speech,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  &quot;O bloody&quot;?Â  But we occasionally find in our early dramatists\n<br>Â Â Â Â  lines which are defective in the first syllable; and in some\n<br>Â Â Â Â  of these instances at least it would almost seem that nothing\n<br>Â Â Â Â  has been omitted by the transcriber or printer.â]\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000249",
