            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"foot\"><span class=\"c3\">105</span> (<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000030\">return</$link>)<br>\n[ Enter the SEVEN DEADLY SINSâ In THE HISTORY OF DR. FAUSTUS, Lucifer amuses Faustus, not by calling up the Seven Deadly Sins, but by making various devils appear before him, &quot;one after another, in forme as they were in hell.&quot; &quot;First entered Beliall in forme of a beare,&quot; &amp;c.â&quot;after him came Beelzebub, in curled haire of a horseflesh colour,&quot; &amp;c.â&quot;then came Astaroth, in the forme of a worme,&quot; &amp;c. &amp;c. During this exhibition, &quot;Lucifer himselfe sate in manner of a man all hairy, but of browne colour, like a squirrell, curled, and his tayle turning upward on his backe as the squirrels use: I think he could crack nuts too like a squirrell.&quot; Sig. D, ed. 1648.]</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000251",
