        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"foot\"><span class=\"c3\">109</span> (<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000031\">return</$link>)<br>\n[ Away, to hell, to hellâ In 4to 1604, these words stand on a line by themselves, without a prefix. (In the later 4tos, the corresponding passage is as follows; &quot;âââ begins with Lechery.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">\n<br>Â Â Â Â  LUCIFER. Away to hell, away!Â  On, piper!Â  [Exeunt the SINS.\n<br>Â Â Â Â  FAUSTUS. O, how this sight doth delight my soul!&quot; &amp;c.)]\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000260": {
