            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">Â Â Â  [Note ||, from page 18 (The First Part of Tamburlaine The\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Great):\n<br>\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Barbarousâ Qy. &quot;O Barbarous&quot;? in the next line but one,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  &quot;O treacherous&quot;? and in the last line of the speech,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  &quot;O bloody&quot;?Â  But we occasionally find in our early dramatists\n<br>Â Â Â Â  lines which are defective in the first syllable; and in\n<br>Â Â Â Â  some of these instances at least it would almost seem that\n<br>Â Â Â Â  nothing has been omitted by the transcriber or printer.â]\n<br></div></div>"
        },
