        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/65fb807d23063af6/text/000000357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-65fb807d23063af6-7a2b93 twpub-65fb807d23063af6-de533d twpub-65fb807d23063af6-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">Â Â Â  [Note || from page 68 (The Second Part of Tamburlaine the\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Great):\n<br>\n<br>Â Â Â Â  Vileâ The 8vo &quot;Vild&quot;; the 4to &quot;Wild&quot; (Both eds. a little\n<br>Â Â Â Â  before, have &quot;VILE monster, born of some infernal hag&quot;, and,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  a few lines after, &quot;To VILE and ignominious servitude&quot;:âthe\n<br>Â Â Â Â  fact is, our early writers (or rather transcribers), with\n<br>Â Â Â Â  their usual inconsistency of spelling, give now the one form,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  and now the other:Â  compare the folio SHAKESPEARE, 1623,\n<br>Â Â Â Â  where we sometimes find &quot;vild&quot; and sometimes &quot;VILE.&quot;)â]\n<br></div></div>"
        },
